.TH HASH-SHELL 1 "January 2026" "hash-shell 29" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
hash-shell \- modern command line interpreter for Linux, macOS, and BSD
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B hash-shell
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B hash-shell
is a comprehensive C-based command line shell interpreter for Linux, macOS,
and BSD, providing a modern, secure, and POSIX-compliant alternative to 
traditional shells.
.SH FEATURES
.TP
.B Tab Completion
Complete commands, files, and directories with the Tab key.
.TP
.B Pipes
Connect commands with | operator.
.TP
.B I/O Redirection
Redirect input (<), output (>), append (>>), and stderr (2>).
.TP
.B Command Chaining
Chain commands with && (and), || (or), and ; (sequential).
.TP
.B Aliases
Define command shortcuts in ~/.hashrc.
.TP
.B Variable Expansion
Use $VAR and ${VAR} syntax for environment variables.
.TP
.B Command History
Navigate history with arrow keys. Supports !!, !n, and !prefix.
.TP
.B Customizable Prompts
Configure PS1 with \\w, \\W, \\u, \\h, \\g (git), and more.
.TP
.B Git Integration
Show branch and status in prompt with \\g escape.
.SH FILES
.TP
.I ~/.hashrc
User configuration file. Loaded on startup.
.TP
.I ~/.hash_history
Command history file.
.SH ENVIRONMENT
.TP
.B HISTSIZE
Maximum commands in memory (default: 1000).
.TP
.B HISTFILESIZE
Maximum commands in history file (default: 2000).
.TP
.B HISTCONTROL
History behavior: ignorespace, ignoredups, ignoreboth, erasedups.
.TP
.B PS1
Prompt string format.
.SH EXAMPLES
.TP
Start hash shell:
.B hash-shell
.TP
Change default shell:
.B chsh -s /usr/bin/hash-shell
